# College Baseball (BSI Priority Sport)

This is the core differentiator: "The college baseball coverage ESPN won't give you."

## Data sources (priority order)
1. NCAA official stats API
2. D1Baseball
3. Baseball America
4. Conference-specific feeds

## Required data points for games
- Full box scores (batting lines, pitching lines, defensive stats)
- RPI and ranking context
- Conference standings impact
- Weather conditions (if available)

## Required data points for players
- Standard slash line (AVG/OBP/SLG)
- Advanced metrics when available (wOBA, wRC+, FIP)
- Draft projections for eligible players
- Transfer portal status

## Display conventions
- Always show conference alongside team name
- Include ranking badge if team is ranked
- Show "vs" for home games, "@" for away
- Timestamps in America/Chicago

## Content priorities
1. Live game coverage with box scores
2. Standings and rankings
3. Player stats and comparisons
4. Recruiting and portal tracking
5. Draft coverage

## Testing requirements
- Validate box score completeness
- Test conference standings calculations
- Verify ranking display accuracy
